==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Firmness
<hw>Firm"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or quality of being
firm.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- <er>Firmness</er>, <er>Constancy</er>.</syn>
<usage> <xex>Firmness</xex> belongs to the will, and
<xex>constancy</xex> to the affections and principles; the former
prevents us from yielding, and the latter from fluctuating. Without
<xex>firmness</xex> a man has no character; ⟦ldquo⟧without
<xex>constancy</xex>,⟦rdquo⟧ says Addison, ⟦ldquo⟧there is neither love,
friendship, nor virtue in the world.⟦rdquo⟧</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Firms</ent>⟦br⟧
